<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 12:55AM CDT  by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Guadalupe, northeastern Bexar and southern Comal Counties through 145
AM CDT...
At 1255 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Smithson Valley, or 9 miles southwest of Canyon Lake Dam, moving
southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
New Braunfels, Schertz, Seguin, Cibolo, Selma, Canyon Lake, Bulverde,
Garden Ridge, McQueeney, Marion, Santa Clara, New Berlin, Smithson
Valley, Geronimo, Zuehl, Spring Branch, Timberwood Park, Startzville,
Specht Store and Freiheit.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
